<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870416-0108 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:Legislating Equity Losses</HL><DD> 04/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION (FTC) </IN><TEXT>   A Federal Trade Commission report has concluded that in the three days surrounding passage of New York's 1985 takeover law, the shareholders of 94 firms experienced a loss in equity value of $1.2 billion. The law &quot;reduced the likelihood that takeovers would occur,&quot; one of the authors of the report said. &quot;You would expect in general that that would reduce the value of the shares of firms that might have been subject to takeovers.&quot; We guess that leaves shareholders with one target: the people responsible for these laws. </TEXT></DOC>